Definition: or (by permutation) זִיד; a primitive root; to seethe; figuratively, to be insolent; be proud, deal proudly, presume, (come) presumptuously, sod.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h2102}}; to be proud; in pride.
from {{h2100}}; a seminal or menstrual flux; issue.
apparently from the same root as {{h2099}} (in the sense of prominence); an angle (as projecting), i.e. (by implication) a corner-column (or anta); corner(stone).
a primitive root (compare {{h2151}}); probably to shake out, i.e. (by implication) to scatter profusely; figuratively, to treat lightly; lavish, despise.
plural probably from the same as {{h2123}}; prominent; Zuzites, an aboriginal tribe of Palestine; Zuzims.
of uncertain origin; Zocheth, an Israelite; Zoheth.
from {{h2107}}; probably scattering, i.e. removal; used adverbially, except; beside, but, only, save.
a primitive root; perhaps properly, to be plump, i.e. (transitively) to nourish; feed.
from {{h2111}} (in the sense of {{h3154}}); perspiration; sweat.
by transposition for {{h2113}}; agitation, maltreatment; × removed, trouble.
from {{h2186}}; rejected; Zanoach, the name of two places in Palestine; Zanoah.
from {{h2181}}; adultery; figuratively, idolatry; whoredom.
from {{h2179}} (in the original sense of flapping); the tail (literally or figuratively); tail.

a primitive root [highly fed and therefore wanton]; to commit adultery (usually of the female, and less often of simple fornication, rarely of involuntary ravishment); figuratively, to commit idolatry (the Jewish people being regarded as the spouse of Jehovah); (cause to) commit fornication, × continually, × great, (be an, play the) harlot, (cause to be, play the) whore, (commit, fall to) whoredom, (cause to) go a-whoring, whorish.
a primitive root meaning to push aside, i.e.; reject, forsake, fail; cast away (off), remove far away (off).
a primitive root; properly, to draw together the feet (as an animal about to dart upon its prey), i.e. to spring forward; leap.
from {{h2181}}; adultery, i.e. (figuratively) infidelity, idolatry; whoredom.
regarded by some as if from {{h2109}} or an unused root, and applied to military equipments; but evidently the feminine plural active participle of {{h2181}}; harlots; armour.
from {{h2142}}; mindful; Zakkur, the name of seven Israelites; Zaccur, Zacchur.
properly, passive participle of {{h2142}}, but used for {{h2145}}; a male (of man or animals); males, men-children.
from {{h2135}}; properly, transparency, i.e. glass; crystal.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h2135}}; purity; innocency.
a primitive root (compare {{h2141}}); to be translucent; figuratively, to be innocent; be (make) clean, cleanse, be clear, count pure.
from {{h2141}}; clear; clean, pure.
from {{h2132}}; olive grove; Zethan, an Israelite; Zethan.
probably from an unused root (akin to {{h2099}}); an olive (as yielding illuminating oil), the tree, the branch or the berry; olive (tree, -yard), Olivet.

(Isaiah 50:11) (feminine); and זִק; or זֵק; from {{h2187}}; properly, what leaps forth, i.e. flash of fire, or a burning arrow; also (from the original sense of the root) a bond; chain, fetter, firebrand, spark.
patrial from {{h2128}}; a Ziphite or inhabitant of Ziph; Ziphim, Ziphite.
from the same as {{h2203}}; flowing; Ziph, the name of a place in Palestine; also of an Israelite; Ziph.
feminine of {{h2128}}; a flowing; Ziphah, an Israelite; Ziphah.
feminine active participle of {{h2119}}; crawling (i.e. serpent); Zocheleth, a boundary stone in. Palestine; Zoheleth.
from {{h2102}}; boiling of water, i.e. wave; proud.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h2099}}; (figuratively) cheerfulness; brightness, countenance.
from an unused root apparently meaning to be conspicuous; fulness of the breast; also a moving creature; abundance, wild beast.
apparently from the same as {{h2123}}; prominence; Ziza, the name of two Israelites; Ziza.
another form for {{h2124}}; Zizah, an Israelite; Zizah.
from {{h2109}}; well-fed; or perhaps an orthographical error for {{h2124}}; Zina, an Israelite; Zina.
from {{h2111}}; agitation; Zia, an Israelite; Zia.
from {{h2168}}; a twig (as pruned); branch.
or זָמִר; and (feminine) זְמִרָה; from {{h2167}}; a song to be accompanied with instrumental music; psalm(-ist), singing, song.
the same as {{h2154}}; Zimmah, the name of two Israelites; Zimmah.
or זַמָּה; from {{h2161}}; a plan, especially a bad one; heinous crime, lewd(-ly, -ness), mischief, purpose, thought, wicked (device, mind, -ness).
from {{h2161}}; intriguing; a Zamzumite, or native tribe of Palestine; Zamzummim.
or זְמֹרָה (feminine); and זְמֹר (masculine); from {{h2168}}; a twig (as pruned); vine, branch, slip.
a primitive root (compare {{h2107}}); to shake (as in the wind), i.e. to quake; figuratively, to be loose morally, worthless or prodigal; blow down, glutton, riotous (eater), vile.
by reduplication from {{h2151}}; tremulous, i.e. a twig; sprig.
; from an unused root apparently meaning to trickle, as myrrh; fragrant dropping; Zilpah, Leah's maid; Zilpah.
or זִלְעָפָהxlit zilʻâphâph corrected to zilʻâphâh; from {{h2196}}; a glow (of wind or anger); also a famine (as consuming); horrible, horror, terrible.
or זְכַרְיָהוּ; from {{h2142}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has remembered; Zecarjah, the name of twenty-nine Israelites; Zachariah, Zechariah.
from {{h2151}}; properly, a shaking, i.e. perhaps a tempest; vilest.
from {{h2142}}; a memento (or memorable thing, day or writing); memorial, record.
from {{h2142}}; memorable; Zicri, the name of twelve Israelites; Zichri.
the same as {{h2143}}; Zeker, an Israelite; Zeker.
from {{h2142}}; properly, remembered, i.e. a male (of man or animals, as being the most noteworthy sex); × him, male, man(child, -kind).

a primitive root; also as denominative from {{h2145}}; properly, to mark (so as to be recognized), i.e. to remember; by implication, to mention; to be male; × burn (incense), × earnestly, be male, (make) mention (of), be mindful, recount, record(-er), remember, make to be remembered, bring (call, come, keep, put) to (in) remembrance, × still, think on, × well.
or זֶכֶר; from {{h2142}}; a memento, abstractly recollection (rarely if ever); by implication, commemoration; memorial, memory, remembrance, scent.
from {{h2141}}; pure; Zakkai, an Israelite; Zaccai.
a primitive root (compare {{h2135}}); to be transparent or clean (phys. or morally); be (make) clean, be pure(-r).
a primitive root meaning to wag; used only as a denominative from {{h2180}}; to curtail, i.e. cut off the rear; smite the hindmost.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h2177}}; sort; kind.
from {{h2168}}; pruned (i.e. choice) fruit; best fruit.
from {{h2167}}; a musical piece or song to be accompanied by an instrument; melody, psalm.
(Aramaic) from the same as {{h2170}}; an instrumental musician; singer.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h2167}}; instrumental music; musick.
from {{h2109}}; properly, nourished (or fully developed), i.e. a form or sort; divers kinds, × all manner of store.
from {{h2167}}; instrumental music; by implication, praise; song.
from {{h2167}}; musical; Zimran, a son of Abraham by Keturah; Zimran.
from {{h2167}}; musical; Zimri, the name of five Israelites, and of an Arabian tribe; Zimri.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h2163}}; to agree (on a time and place); prepare.
from {{h2163}}; an appointed occasion; season, time.
(Aramaic) from {{h2165}}; the same as {{h2165}}; season, time.

a primitive root (perhaps identical with {{h2168}} through the idea of striking with the fingers); properly, to touch the strings or parts of a musical instrument, i.e. play upon it; to make music, accompanied by the voice; hence to celebrate in song and music; give praise, sing forth praises, psalms.
feminine of {{h2158}}; song; Zemirah, an Israelite; Zemira.
a primitive root; to plan, usually in a bad sense; consider, devise, imagine, plot, purpose, think (evil).
from {{h2161}}; a plot; wicked device.
a primitive root; to fix (a time); appoint.
a primitive root (compare {{h2167}}, {{h5568}}, {{h6785}}); to trim (a vine); prune.
apparently from {{h2167}} or {{h2168}}; a gazelle (from its lightly touching the ground); chamois.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h2199}}; to make an outcry; cry.
a primitive root; properly, to shake off, i.e. (figuratively) to agitate (as with fear); move, tremble, vex.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h2109}}; feed.
from {{h2111}}; agitation, fear; be removed, trouble, vexation. Compare {{h2189}}.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h2111}}; to shake (with fear); tremble.
a primitive root (compare {{h6695}}); to press together, tighten; close, rush, thrust together.

a primitive root; to turn aside (especially for lodging); hence to be a foreigner, strange, profane; specifically (active participle) to commit adultery; (come from) another (man, place), fanner, go away, (e-) strange(-r, thing, woman).
probably from the root of {{h2123}}; prominent; Zaza, an Israelite; Zaza.
from {{h2115}}; trodden on; that which is crushed.
a primitive root; to crawl; by implication, to fear; be afraid, serpent, worm.
a primitive root; to shove or displace; loose.

a primitive root; to shriek (from anguish or danger); by analogy, (as a herald) to announce or convene publicly; assemble, call (together), (make a) cry (out), come with such a company, gather (together), cause to be proclaimed.
from {{h2196}}; angry; displeased.
from an unused root (akin (by permutation) to {{h6819}}), meaning to dwindle; small; little.
from {{h2111}}; disquiet; Zaavan, an Idumaean; Zaavan.
a primitive root; to extinguish; be extinct.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h2191}}; little.
from {{h2194}}; strictly froth at the mouth, i.e. (figuratively) fury (especially of God's displeasure with sin); angry, indignation, rage.
a primitive root; properly, to foam at the mouth, i.e. to be enraged; abhor, abominable, (be) angry, defy, (have) indignation.
from {{h2196}}; anger; indignation, rage(-ing), wrath.
a primitive root; properly, to boil up, i.e. (figuratively) to be peevish or angry; fret, sad, worse liking, be wroth.
